# CI/CD Practice Project

A Python web application demonstrating a full CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions.

## 🚀 Live Demo
[View Live App](https://cicd-practice-xolu.onrender.com)

## ⚙️ Pipeline Features
- ✅ Automated testing with pytest on every push
- ✅ Code style enforcement with flake8
- ✅ Matrix builds across Python 3.9, 3.10, and 3.11
- ✅ Docker image automatically built and pushed to Docker Hub
- ✅ Automatic deployment to Render on every merge to main

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- **Language:** Python 3.11
- **Web Framework:** Flask
- **Server:** Gunicorn
- **Containerisation:** Docker
- **CI/CD:** GitHub Actions
- **Hosting:** Render

## 🔄 How the Pipeline Works
Every time code is pushed to `main`, GitHub Actions automatically:
1. Sets up Python 3.9, 3.10, and 3.11 in parallel
2. Installs all dependencies
3. Runs the linter (flake8) to enforce code style
4. Runs all tests (pytest)
5. Builds a Docker image and pushes it to Docker Hub
6. Render detects the new image and deploys automatically

## 🏃 Run Locally
```bash
git clone https://github.com/robgotherearly/cicd-practice.git
cd cicd-practice
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

## 🐳 Run with Docker
```bash
docker pull robgotherearly/cicd-practice:latest
docker run -p 8000:8000 robgotherearly/cicd-practice:latest
```